Davis Selected Advisers - Wikipedia





















 






Davis Selected Advisers

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

Davis Selected Advisers is an independent investment firm based in Tucson, Arizona.
The firm was established by Shelby Davis in 1969 whose father Shelby Cullom Davis was a well known investment adviser to major political figures, and who over a 50 year period had reportedly turned a $100,000 investment into $800 million. He was also the United States Ambassador to Switzerland.
The company operates several types of funds, from large cap blend to multi-cap international. According to the company's web site, two of the senior executives have the last name Davis.
External links[edit]

Davis Funds http://www.davisfunds.com/probios.html





 
